column10:
Goods- 
gameplay; 
patches; 
graphics; 
cinematics

Bads- 
30 fps locked main menu, fatalities, intros and invasions mode; 
story was so-so (like the main villain has no significant motive to do whatever he's doing)
pricing as compared to previous entries at launch (in my region,India, at least)
Megan Fox

I love this game, but in the state its in on pc right now, i cant recommend it;
I have a beefy computer and it takes 2-3 minutes just to go onto the character customisation screen and when playing the game and going through the new mode, it runs like anus.
I would have at least 200 hours on this game if this game didnt do what every other game does when it ports to pc and run like cancer.

Nope sorry, but MK11 and Injustice 2 was better than this. 
---
Here's why:
1. Microtransaction a bit too much this time;
[strike]2. No clash system. Kombatan's dialogue can only be heard in local fight. Not invasion nor tower; [/strike]

[strike]3. Chances for skin & gear drop is lowered and it can only be obtained via Invasion, shrine, and store;[/strike] 
4. Only 2 options for kustomizing your fighters, their weapon and their skin;
5. Lack of obtainable skin atm. Most unique skins can only be obtained via Store with real money;
6. Kombat XPs a bit grindy atm;   
7. No CPU vs CPU fight;
---
For now this is my current issue for the game. Let's just hope the best for MK1 in the next 2 years.
